    "In this case, our null hypothesis is a GWB from a population of GW-driven circular SMBHBs parameterised only by the PSD amplitude log 10 A of Eq.",
    "(3) (we fix γ = 13/3).",
    "We run several analyses with a fixed n T for the inflationary background, sampling over (log 10 r, log 10 A).",
    "For each of the n T values, we obtain a distribution for log 10 r and take the 95% quantile as an upper bound.",
    "As found in Lasky et al. (2016), n T and the log 10 r upper bounds are related with good precision by a linear relation:"
